@NODE "INTRO" "InTroDuCTiOn"
@TOC "MAIN"
(-) InTRoDuCTiOn  (-)

In shorts I'll tell you the story of this unexpected V2.0 of My COol DiarY,
a  little freeware utility released about a year ago by Digital Chaos.  One
day  kRs/DTC found in the chaos of his HD the source of McD 1.4, written by
another  DTC guy, LrY.  He knew some people were using that program, but he
also   knew   that  it  could  have  been  much  better  with  some  little
improvements.   So  he  decided  to  make  them  and he rewrote most of the
original  code,  speeding up, debugging and improving it..  You can see the
result in this new 2.0 version...  Use 'n' EnJoY It..
@ENDNODE

@NODE "USAGE" "UsAGe"
@TOC "MAIN"
(-) UsAGE (-)

This  is  an  easy2use  userfriendly program, so I think there's no need to
explain  in  details  all  its options..  You should understand them all by
yourself..   Anyway  in  the main menu you can choose to create a new diary
(the  .McD extension will be added) or load and use an old diary.  McD V1.4
used  a  prefs  file  to  store  field  names, from V2.0 this file has been
removed,  anyway V2.0 is still able to read old diaries with .prefs files..
The sort option isnt very fast, in other words it's very slow, but at least
it  works fine =).  Clicking in the status textfield you can enter a search
string, clicking the Search button you can repeat the search..
Now go exploring all the features of this COol program.. ;)

@ENDNODE

